########################################
#How to use MYUTILS
########################################

Go into MYUTILS folder. make.

Add path to the executables to your bashrc:
MYUTILSPATH="path/to/myutils
export PATH=$PATH:$MYUTILSPATH/bin

source ~/.bashrc

######################################
# Useful ~/.bashrc functions        
######################################

To make use of functions such as 
- sunimage: wrapper around nimage to see 3D files
- plotgeometry: plot src, rec on top of 2D model

Run "source useful_bashrc.sh", or paste the functions on your bashrc, or add 

source /path/to/myutils/useful_bashrc.sh 

to your bashrc, then "source ~/.bashrc".
